quran[17]{c,v,t}:
  25,61,Blessed is He who appointed houses in the sky and set in it a lamp and a shining moon
  25,62,"It is He who made the night and the day alternate for someone who desires to take admonition, or desires to give thanks"
  25,63,"The servants of the All-beneficent are those who walk humbly on the earth, and when the ignorant address them, say, ‘Peace!’"
  25,64,"Those who spend the night for their Lord, prostrating and standing [in worship]"
  25,65,"Those who say, ‘Our Lord! Turn away from us the punishment of hell. Indeed its punishment is enduring"
  25,66,Indeed it is an evil station and abode.’
  25,67,"Those who are neither wasteful nor tightfisted when spending, but balanced between these [two extremes]"
  25,68,"Those who do not invoke another deity besides Allah, and do not kill a soul [whose life] Allah has made inviolable, except with due cause, and do not commit fornication. (Whoever does that shall encounter its retribution)"
  25,69,the punishment being doubled for him on the Day of Resurrection. In it he will abide in humiliation forever
  25,70,"except those who repent, attain faith, and act righteously. For such, Allah will replace their misdeeds with good deeds, and Allah is all-forgiving, all-merciful"
  25,71,And whoever repents and acts righteously indeed turns to Allah with due penitence
  25,72,"Those who do not give false testimony, and when they come upon frivolity, pass by with dignity"
  25,73,"Those who, when reminded of the signs of their Lord, do not turn a deaf ear and a blind eye to them"
  25,74,"And those who say, ‘Our Lord! Give us joy and comfort in our spouses and offspring, and make us imams of the Godwary.’"
  25,75,"Those shall be rewarded with sublime abodes for their patience and steadfastness, and they shall be met there with greetings and ‘Peace,’"
  25,76,"to abide in them [forever], an excellent station and abode"
  25,77,"Say, ‘Were it not for the sake of summoning you [to faith], what store my Lord would have set by you? But you impugned [me and my summons], so it will soon follow as a result.’"